               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000064d-1" xml:lang="en"></p>Longxingsi Mituodian (Amitabha Hall)was added to the north side of the Dabeige in the fifth year of the Ming dynasty 
                  Zhengde reign period (1510). Jingyetang and Yaoshidian are located on the east and west sides, respectively. The Amitabha hall is five bays (23.1 m) across the front 
                  facade, has a depth of four bays (14.52 m), and is crowned with a single-eaves hip-gable (xieshan 歇山) roof covered with green tiles. Its face width is 23.1 meters and 
                  its depth is 14.52 meters. The overall height of the building is 16.1 meters. </p>
                  <p source="#bibl000064d-1" xml:lang="en"></p> In front of the hall is a “moon terrace” (yuetai 月臺)’s east-west width is 29.25 meters, and the north-south length is 9.53 meters. 
                  The three sides, east, west, and south sides have treadways. The eaves do not have bracket-block clusters (dougong 斗栱) but put the Ming Dynasty’s commonly used large forehead tie 
                  beams (efang 額枋), small forehead tie beams (efang 額枋), and other beams (e 額) between the pillars. The front room of the main hall has six square lattices of windows, the upper part 
                  has the horizontal pi window, and the window center (chuangxin 窗心) for a diagonal square lattice. The left and right rooms have four Jian windows.
                  Inside the hall, the Amitabha statue is seated on the 1.57-meter-high stone Sumeru-style Buddha altar. Amitabha has a wide forehead and huge ears, with eyes downcast, wearing a robe, 
                  hands folded in front of the abdomen for meditation seal, and sitting on a lotus seat. It is at 3.39 meters high (Zhang et al., eds. 2000, 18).</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000064d-1" xml:lang="en"></p>彌陀殿位於隆興寺大悲閣北面的中軸線上，是明正德五年（公元1510年）增建的。凈業堂、藥師殿並列於東西兩側。此殿為一座面闊五間，進深四間，青瓦覆頂的單檐歇山式建築。
                  通面闊23.1米，通進深14.52米。自室外地皮至大吻上皮通高16.1米。殿前月臺東西寬29.25米，南北長9.53米，東、西、南三面設垂帶踏道。檐下不設鬥拱，而將明代慣用的大額枋、小額枋及由額、墊板和平板枋等構件疊置於柱於柱之間。
                  大殿正面明間設六抹方格格扇門四扇，中上檻之間設置橫披窗，窗心為斜方格。左右兩次間裝四抹檻窗各四扇。殿內1.57米高的石須彌座式佛壇上供阿彌陀佛塑像。阿彌陀佛肉髻螺發，額寬耳垂，雙目俯視，身披袈裟，
                  雙手疊置於腹前作禪定印，高坐於蓮座，高3.39米。（河北省正定縣文物保管所 2000, 18）</p>
